      "text": {
        "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>Rectangles <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/2/9/b/29b16bf008f507f2c3876bc743f9058ecb7b5af7.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$BCC_1B_2,$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"74\" height=\"16\" /> <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/f/1/6/f1622e15f29040cc3d0ad7e9aab99fe6e983e759.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$CAA_1C_2,$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"73\" height=\"16\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/7/c/d/7cd1d5a14692916a1824c952e77a5d3d2d82e499.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$ABB_1A_2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"69\" height=\"15\" /> are erected outside an acute triangle <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/b/d/2/bd222166def59a3315433877917a826de6488031.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$ABC.$\" width=\"45\" height=\"13\" /> Suppose that<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/3/7/3378f0c4409d14bc0afddf2616992c13f624be3b.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[\\angle BC_1C+\\angle CA_1A+\\angle AB_1B=180^{\\circ}.\\]\" width=\"293\" height=\"16\" />Prove that lines <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/d/f/5/df5b6d99e91936a974c9f93bfe2bd3b9f6b8156b.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$B_1C_2,$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"45\" height=\"16\" /> <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/0/b/10b85bab40fe89e79163c476adadb6b5604706ff.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$C_1A_2,$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"48\" height=\"18\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/d/b/1dbd68bf0453f67a0e5ff57ccf9a818a835788a3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$A_1B_2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"41\" height=\"15\" /> are concurrent.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Solution\">Solution</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=2021_USAMO_Problems/Problem_1&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Solution\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"floatright\"><a href=\"/wiki/index.php/File:2021_USAMO_1.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"2021 USAMO 1.png\" src=\"https://wiki-images.artofproblemsolving.com//thumb/b/bf/2021_USAMO_1.png/400px-2021_USAMO_1.png\" width=\"400\" height=\"426\" srcset=\"https://wiki-images.artofproblemsolving.com//thumb/b/bf/2021_USAMO_1.png/600px-2021_USAMO_1.png 1.5x, https://wiki-images.artofproblemsolving.com//b/bf/2021_USAMO_1.png 2x\" /></a></div>\n<p>Let <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/f/f/9ffb448918db29f2a72f8f87f421b3b3cad18f95.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$D$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"17\" height=\"14\" /> be the second point of intersection of the circles <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/c/9/6/c96123d4f97bd681443eab8f6eeb51dd7869ba50.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$AB_1B$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"49\" height=\"15\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/d/1/3d1acee10ed0631cf59da31ae385cc88f41a1e9d.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$AA_1C.$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"55\" height=\"17\" /> Then:\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/a/e/0ae1ac0187c65428471e44dcb190b643433b5cbb.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\begin{align*} \\angle ADB &amp;= 180^\\circ – \\angle AB_1B,&amp;\\angle ADC &amp;= 180^\\circ – \\angle AA_1C\\\\ \\angle BDC &amp;= 360^\\circ – \\angle ADB – \\angle ADC\\\\ &amp;= 360^\\circ – (180^\\circ – \\angle AB_1B) – (180^\\circ – \\angle AA_1C)\\\\ &amp;= \\angle AB_1B + \\angle AA_1C\\\\ \\angle BDC + \\angle BC_1C &amp;= 180^\\circ \\end{align*}\" width=\"663\" height=\"115\" />\nTherefore, <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/7/c/87c48194ed0489c3aa96cbecf391a3c2f5a504a3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$BDCC_1B_2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"88\" height=\"17\" /> is cyclic with diameters <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/6/8/168608dcef0e370f34a7b4755c6bb4ffe626c0c9.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$BC_1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"33\" height=\"15\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/f/1/1f190d696bce327933baee9d5780000b1da898dd.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$CB_2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"37\" height=\"17\" />, and thus <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/6/8/a/68a2c011be5ff266f6f484ce8546b6a91eab57ee.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\angle CDB_2 = 90^\\circ.$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"121\" height=\"18\" />\nSimilarly, <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/8/4/08431cc9b84f71b51b5ef4856d512bd0a9d68af2.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\angle CDA_1 = 90^\\circ$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"116\" height=\"18\" />, meaning points <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/6/c/36c7f3f828cf12ab9cafeffad282468a95219600.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$A_1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"19\" height=\"15\" />, <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/f/f/9ffb448918db29f2a72f8f87f421b3b3cad18f95.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$D$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"17\" height=\"14\" />, and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/6/8/368b6f971b418d731c62ff2cb59f51c527d22849.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$B_2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"20\" height=\"15\" /> are collinear.\n</p><p>Similarly, the points <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/2/e/0/2e024865e29a0f84fe948a7e7db809293b99ec60.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$A_2, D, C_1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"75\" height=\"18\" /> and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/e/9/4e93d12a6fdc73c085bc1af5ab5fc7d841cf36da.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$C_2, D, B_1$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"75\" height=\"18\" /> are collinear.\n</p><p>(After USAMO 2021 Solution Notes – Evan Chen)\n</p><p><b>vladimir.shelomovskii@gmail.com, vvsss</b>\n</p><p>The problems on this page are copyrighted by the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.maa.org\">Mathematical Association of America</a>'s <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://maa.org/student-programs/amc/\">American Mathematics Competitions</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/File:AMC_logo.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"AMC logo.png\" src=\"https://wiki-images.artofproblemsolving.com//8/8b/AMC_logo.png\" width=\"97\" height=\"84\" style=\"vertical-align: middle\" /></a>\n</p>\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240908060020\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.040 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.041 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 120/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 460/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 243/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 4228/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    1.069      1 Template:MAA_Notice\n100.00%    1.069      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki-wiki_:pcache:idhash:19897-0!canonical and timestamp 20240908060020 and revision id 208379\n -->\n"
